    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The compiler has different stages. If there has been an error inside one stage, the subsequent stages are not executed. This mechanism ensures that if a stage completes, the information it generates inside the AST annotations are always complete. For example, after the typechecker has run, you can be sure that every expression has an assigned type.\r\n\r\nWe can debate if some of the errors should allow subsequent stages to run, but to be honest, why not just fix the errors?",
